{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_94","type":"agent_message","text":"The remaining strong candidate is `EquinoxFactoryManager`: it runs after log services start, it is full of uncovered reflective URL-factory access in the dynamic-access report, and a failure there could roll the system bundle back and make `LoggerAdmin` disappear without changing the first trace output. I’m extracting the exact JDK fields/methods it touches so I can add targeted metadata instead of widening the file blindly."}}
